summary: The document describes the capital stock of a company, including 22,593,069 shares of common stock and 865,452 shares of 6.25% Series A Cumulative Redeemable Preferred Stock as of September 30, 2025. The common stock has equal rights to earnings, dividends, and voting, while the preferred stock has a fixed dividend rate of 6.25%, ranks senior to common stock for dividends and liquidation, and includes a share repurchase program with varying discounts based on the holding period.
